					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A demo with multiple variable split points uses a lot of CPU time, as it would have to spin a lot longer to wait for the right line. But the letterbox demo (two fixed split points) uses 20 IRQs per frame, most of which take only about 36 cycles (if I remember correctly) to handle. Even counting other overheads, I imagine it's taking less than 5% of CPU time. I'd have to profile it harder to get a more precise figure.</div>

